elected_American_Musicals_by_Richard_Rodgers_Oscar_Hammerstein_II_Arthur_Laurents_Leonard_Bernstein_Stephen_Sondheim_and_James_Lapine.html ''The American Musical''], Tectum Verlag, Marburg, Germany, {{ISBN|3-8288-8458-X}}\n* Bloom, Ken and Vlastnik, Frank.  ''Broadway Musicals:  The 101 Greatest Shows of All Time''.  New York:  Black Dog & Leventhal Publishers, 2004.  {{ISBN|978-1-57912-390-1}}.\n* Ewen, David. ''With a Song in His Heart (Richard Rodgers)''. New York: Holt, Rinehart and Winston, 1963.\n* Green, Stanley. ''The Rodgers and Hammerstein Fact Book''. Milwaukee: Hal Leonard, 1980.\n* Martin, Mary. ''My Hearts Belongs'' (Autobiography). New York: William Morrow & Co., Inc., 1976.\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|South Pacific (musical)}}\n* {{ibdb show|8197|title=South Pacific}}\n* [http://www.rnh.com/show/97/South-Pacific ''South Pacific''] at the Rodgers and Hammerstein Organization\n* [http://www.guidetomusicaltheatre.com/shows_s/south_pacific.htm ''South Pacific''] at the Guide to Musical Theatre\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110521101908/http://stageagent.com/Shows/View/749 ''South Pacific''] at StageAgent.com\n\n{{Tales of the South Pacific}}\n{{Rodgers and Hammerstein}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards for ''South Pacific''\n| list =\n{{DramaDesk MusicalRevival 2001\u20132025}}\n{{Pulitzer Prize for Drama 1926-1950}}\n{{TonyAwardBestMusical 1947-1975}}\n{{TonyAward MusicalRevival}}\n{{TonyAward MusicalBook 1947-1975}}\n{{TonyAward MusicalScore 1947-1975}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:South Pacific (Musical)}}\n[[Category:1949 musicals]]\n[[Category:Musicals about World War II]]\n[[Category:Broadway musicals]]\n[[Category:Drama Desk Award-winning musicals]]\n[[Category:Pulitzer Prize for Drama-winning works]]\n[[Category:Musicals by Rodgers and Hammerstein]]\n[[Category:Musicals based on short fiction]]\n[[Category:Pulitzer Prize for Drama-winning musicals]]\n[[Category:Pacific theatre of World War II]]\n[[Category:Oceania 