rld Championships in Athletics|World Championships]]\n|[[Beijing, China]]\n|47th (h)\n|200 m\n|[[2015 World Championships in Athletics \u2013 Men's 200 metres|21.36]]\n|-\n|2016\n|[[2016 Asian Indoor Athletics Championships|Asian Indoor Championships]]\n|[[Doha, Qatar]]\n|7th\n|60 m\n|[[2016 Asian Indoor Athletics Championships \u2013 Results#60 meters|6.89]]\n|-\n|2016\n|[[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]]\n|[[Rio de Janeiro]]\n|69th (h)\n|100 m\n|[[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 100 metres|11.89]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Mohammed Abukhousa}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Abukhousa, Mohammed}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Palestinian male sprinters]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:World Athletics Championships athletes for Palestine]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2014 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2016 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic athletes of Palestine]]\n[[Category:Asian Games competitors for Palestine]]\n\n\n{{Palestine-athletics-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Palestinian athlete}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n| name = Mohammed Abukhousa\n| image =Mohammed Abukhousa Rio 2016.jpg\n| caption =Abukhousa at the 2016 Olympics\n| nationality =Palestinian\n| sport = [[Track and field]]\n| event = 100 m, 200 m\n| club = \n| birth_date ={{birth date and age|1992|12|30|df=yes}}\n| birth_place =\n| residence = \n| death_date = \n| death_place =\n| height = 1.70 m<ref>[http://iis.siccsports.com/Sports/Biographies/Athletes_Profile/?ParticCode=5109909&lang=en ABUKHOUSA Mohammed A A]{{Dead link|date=April 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}. 2014 Asian Games</ref>\n| weight = 67 kg\n}}\n\n'''Mohammed Abukhousa''' (born 30 December 1992) is a Palestinian [[Sprint (running)|sprinter]].<ref name=\"Bio\">{{cite web |url=http://www.iaaf.org/athletes/palestine/mohammed-abukhousa-285030 |title=Mohammed Abukhousa |accessdate=20 August 2013 |work=IAAF}}</ref> He competed at the [[2013 World Championships in Athletics|2013]] and [[2015 World Championships in Athletics|2015 World Championships]] and at the [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Olympics|2016 Summer Olympics]] without advancing from the first round.\n\n==Personal bests==\n'''Outdoor'''\n*[[100 metres]] \u2013 10.55 (-0.3&nbsp;m/s, Strasbourg 2014) '''NR'''\n*[[200 metres]] \u2013 21.26 (-0.3&nbsp;m/s, Colmar 2014) '''NR'''\n'''Indoor'''\n*[[60 metres]] \u2013 6.77 (Doha 2016) '''NR'''\n\n==International competitions==\n{| {{AchievementTable|Event=yes}}\n|-\n!colspan=\"6\"|Representing {{PLE}}\n|-\n|2013\n|[[2013 World Championships in Athletics|World Championships]]\n|[[Moscow, Russia]]\n|14th (p)\n|100 m\n|[[2013 World Championships in Athletics \u2013 Men's 100 metres|10.87]]\n|-\n|2014\n|[[Athletics at the 2014 Asian Games|Asian Games]]\n|[[Incheon, South Korea]]\n|20th (h)\n|100 m\n|[[Athletics at the 2014 Asian Games \u2013 Men's 100 metres|10.80]]\n|-\n|2015\n|[[2015 World Championships in Athletics|World Championships]]\n|[[Beijing, China]]\n|47th (h)\n|200 m\n|[[2015 World Championships in Athletics \u2013 Men's 200 metres|21.36]]\n|-\n|2016\n|[[2016 Asian Indoor Athletics Championships|Asian Indoor Championships]]\n|[[Doha, Qatar]]\n|7th\n|60 m\n|[[2016 Asian Indoor Athletics Championships \u2013 Results#60 meters|6.89]]\n|-\n|2016\n|[[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Olympics|Olympic Games]]\n|[[Rio de Janeiro]]\n|69th (h)\n|100 m\n|[[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's 100 metres|11.89]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Mohammed Abukhousa}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Abukhousa, Mohammed}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Palestinian male sprinters]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:World Athletics C